\par }{\fcs1 \ai\af0 \fcs0 \cs18\i\insrsid6912711 Knowledge (INT; TRAINED ONLY)}{\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
\par Check: Answering a question within the character's field of study has a DC of 10 (for really easy questions), 15 (for basic questions), or 20 to 30 (for really tough questions).
\par Retry: No. The check represents what the character knows, and thinking about a topic a second time doesn't let the character know something the character never learned in the first place.
\par Special: An untrained Knowledge check is simply an Intelligence check. Without actual training, a character only knows common knowledge.
\par }{\fcs1 \ai\af0 \fcs0 \cs18\i\insrsid6912711 Listen (WIS)}{\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
\par Check: Make a Listen check against a DC that reflects how quiet the noise is that the character might hear or against an opposed Move Silently check.
\par The DM may make the Listen check so that the character doesn't know whether not hearing anything means that nothing is there, or that the character rolled low.
\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx916\tx1832\tx2748\tx3664\tx4580\tx5496\tx6412\tx7328\tx8244\tx9160\tx10076\tx10992\tx11908\tx12824\tx13740\tx14656\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fcs1 \af2\afs20\alang60488 \fcs0 
\f2\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fcs1 \af2 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 DC\~\~\~\~\~ Sound
\par --\~\~\~\~\~ -----
\par 0\~\~\~\~\~\~ People talking
\par 5\~\~\~\~\~\~ A person in medium armor walking at a slow pace
\par \~\~\~\~\~\~\~ (10 ft./round) trying not to make noise.
\par 10\~\~\~\~\~ An unarmored person walking at a slow pace
\par \~\~\~\~\~\~\~ (15 ft./round) trying not to make any noise
\par 15\~\~\~\~\~ A 1st-level rogue using Move Silently within
\par \~\~\~\~\~\~\~ 10 ft. of the listener
