\par +1\~\~\~\~\~ Per 10 ft. from the listener
\par +5\~\~\~\~\~ Through a door
\par +15\~\~\~\~ Through a stone wall
\par }\pard\plain \s17\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang60488 \fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
In the case of people trying to be quiet, the listed DCs could be replaced by Move Silently checks, in which case the listed DC would be the average result (or close to it). 
\par Retry: The character can make a Listen check every time the character has a chance to hear something in a reactive manner. As a full-round action, the character may try to hear something the character failed to hear previously.
\par Special: When several characters are listening to the same thing, the DM can make a single 1d20 roll and use it for all the listeners' skill checks.
\par }{\fcs1 \ai\af0 \fcs0 \cs18\i\insrsid6912711 Move Silently (DEX; ARMOR CHECK PENALTY)}{\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
\par Check: The character's Move Sile
ntly check is opposed by the Listen check of anyone who might hear the character. The character can move up to one-half the character's normal speed at no penalty. At more than one-half and up to the character's full speed, the character suffers a 
\endash 5 penalty. It's practically impossible (\endash 20 penalty) to move silently while running or charging.
\par }{\fcs1 \ai\af0 \fcs0 \cs18\i\insrsid6912711 Open Lock (DEX; TRAINED ONLY)}{\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
