f performance per rank.
\par Check: The character can impress audiences with talent and skill.
\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx916\tx1832\tx2748\tx3664\tx4580\tx5496\tx6412\tx7328\tx8244\tx9160\tx10076\tx10992\tx11908\tx12824\tx13740\tx14656\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fcs1 \af2\afs20\alang60488 \fcs0 
\f2\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fcs1 \af2 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 DC\~\~\~\~\~ Performance
\par --\~\~\~\~\~ -----------
\par 10\~\~\~\~\~ Routine performance. Trying to earn money by playing in public is essentially begging.
\par \tab The character earns 1d10 cp/day.
\par 15\~\~\~\~\~ Enjoyable performance. In a prosperous city, the character can earn 1d10 sp/day.
\par 20\~\~\~\~\~ Great performance. In a prosperous city, the character can earn 3d10 sp/day. 
\par \tab With time, the character may be invited to join a professional troupe and may develop a regional reputation.
\par 25\~\~\~\~\~ Memorable performance. In a prosperous city, the character can earn 1d6 gp/day. 
\par \tab With time, the character may come to the attention of noble patrons and develop a national reputation.
\par 30\~\~\~\~\~ Extraordinary performance. In a prosperous city, the character can earn 3d6 gp/day. 
\par \tab With time, the character may draw attention from distant potential patrons or even from extraplanar beings.
\par }\pard\plain \s17\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang60488 \fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
A masterwork musical instrument gives a +2 circumstance bonus to Perform checks that involve the use of the instrument.
\par Retry: Retries are allowed, but they don't negate previous failures, and an audience that has been unimpressed in the past is going to be prejudiced against future performances. (Increase the DC by 2 for each previous failure.)
\par In addition to using the Perform skill, a character could entertain people with tumbling, tightrope walking, and spells (especially illusions).
\par }{\fcs1 \ai\af0 \fcs0 \cs18\i\insrsid6912711 Pick Pocket (DEX; TRAINED ONLY; ARMOR CHECK PENALTY)}{\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
\par Check: A check against DC 10 lets the character palm a coin-sized, unattended object. Minor feats of legerdemain, such as making a coin disappear, are also DC 10 unless an observer is determined to note where the item went.
\par When performing this skill under close observation, the character's skill check is opposed by the observer's Spot check. The observer's check doesn't prevent the character from performing the action, just from doing it unnoticed.
\par If the character tries to take something from another creature, the character must make a skill check against D
C 20. The opponent makes a Spot check to detect the attempt. The opponent detects the attempt if her check result beats the character's check result, regardless of whether the character got the item.
\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx916\tx1832\tx2748\tx3664\tx4580\tx5496\tx6412\tx7328\tx8244\tx9160\tx10076\tx10992\tx11908\tx12824\tx13740\tx14656\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fcs1 \af2\afs20\alang60488 \fcs0 
\f2\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fcs1 \af2 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 DC\~\~\~\~\~ Task
\par --\~\~\~\~\~ ----
\par 10\~\~\~\~\~ Palm a coin-sized object, make a coin disappear
\par 20\~\~\~\~\~ Lift a small object from a person
\par }\pard\plain \s17\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang60488 \fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
Retry: A second Pick Pocket attempt against the same target, or when being watched by the same observer, has a DC +10 higher than the first skill check if the first check failed or if the attempt was noticed.
\par Special: If the character has 5 or more ranks in Bluff, the character gets a +2 synergy bonus on Pick Pocket checks.
\par }{\fcs1 \ai\af0 \fcs0 \cs18\i\insrsid6912711 Profession (WIS; TRAINED ONLY)}{\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
\par The character is trained in a livelihood or a professional role, such as apothecary, boater, bookkeeper, brewer, cook, driver, farmer, fisher, guide, herbalist, herdsman, innkeeper, lumberjack, miller, miner, porter, rancher, sailor, scribe, siege enginee
r, stablehand, tanner, teamster, woodcutter, and so forth.
\par Like Craft, Profession is actually a number of separate skills. The character could have several Profession skills, each with its own ranks, each purchased as a separate skill.
\par While a Craft skill r
epresents skill in creating or making an item, a Profession skill represents an aptitude in a vocation requiring a broader range of less specific knowledge. To draw a modern analogy, if an occupation is a service industry, it's probably a Profession skill
. If it's in the manufacturing sector, it's probably a Craft skill.
\par Check: The character can practice a trade and make a decent living, earning about half the check result in gold pieces per week of dedicated work. The character knows how to use the tools o
f the trade, how to perform the profession's daily tasks, how to supervise untrained helpers, and how to handle common problems. For example, a sailor knows how to tie several basic knots, how to tend and repair sails, and how to stand a deck watch at sea
. The DM sets DCs for specialized tasks. 
\par Retry: An attempt to use a Profession skill to earn an income cannot be retried. The character is stuck with whatever weekly wage the check result brought the character. (Another check may be made after a week to de
termine a new income for the next period of time.) An attempt to accomplish some specific task can usually be retried.
\par Special: Untrained laborers and assistants earn an average of 1 silver piece per day.
\par }{\fcs1 \ai\af0 \fcs0 \cs18\i\insrsid6912711 Read Lips (INT; TRAINED ONLY; ROGUE ONLY)}{\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid6912711 
\par Check: Th
e character must be within 30 feet of the speaker and be able to see her speak. The character must be able to understand the speaker's language. (Use of this skill is language-dependent.) The base DC is 15, and it is higher for complex speech or an inarti
